.SH Version 5.0.1 (2016\-02\-13)
.SS Major:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Rename \fB\fCbinman snip\fR command to \fB\fCbinman text\fR\&.
.IP \(bu 2
Rename \fB\fCbinman conv\fR command to \fB\fCbinman roff\fR and make it operate on a bin
script containing an embedded manual page rather than the extracted latter.
.IP \(bu 2
Add \fB\fCbinman html\fR command which extracts embedded manual page from a given
bin script, converts it into HTML, and then prints the result to STDOUT.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\fCbinman show\fR now falls back to displaying a temporary HTML manual page if
.BR man (1) 
fails to display the temporary UNIX manual page.  This is useful in
Windows where there is no 
.BR man (1) 
reader, but a web browser can be started.
.IP \(bu 2
When a HTML manual page is shown, \fB\fCbinman\fR now blocks until the launched
web browser exits.  Previously, it used to exit immediately (nonblocking).
.RE
.SH Version 4.2.1 (2016\-02\-12)
.SS Minor:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Add \fB\fCbinman:mkd\fR rake task to extract \fB\fCman/man1/*.1.markdown\fR files.
.RE
.SS Patch:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Shell out to 
.BR md2man-rake (1) 
for dynamic man pages.
.PP
Requiring the md2man/rakefile.rb script builds Rake tasks only once, so
it ignores any man page files generated dynamically after the require().
.PP
This fix shells out to 
.BR md2man-rake (1) 
causing that script to be required
every time afresh, so that such dynamically generated files are handled.
.IP \(bu 2
Failure when \fB\fCbinman help\fR is called without ARGV.
.PP
binman.rb:63:in \fB\fChelp': undefined method\fRindex' for nil:NilClass (NoMethodError)
.IP \(bu 2
Failure when \fB\fCbinman show\fR is called without ARGV.
.PP
binman.rb:47:in `basename': no implicit conversion of IO into String (TypeError)
.IP \(bu 2
Failure when \fB\fCbinman show\fR is given input on STDIN.
.PP
binman.rb:51:in `basename': no implicit conversion of IO into String (TypeError)
.RE
.SS Patch:
.SH Version 4.1.0 (2016\-02\-10)
.SS Minor:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Print path of HTML man page to STDOUT when launching browser.
.RE
.SS Patch:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Revert "ensure 'binman:web' task works the first time thru".
.PP
This reverts commit dd0511e78e02546cac4903b5c6de6243607a8bba,
which was causing the following error under Ruby 2.3.0p0.
.IP
% rake build
mkdir \-p man/man1
rake aborted!
LoadError: cannot load such file \-\- md2man/rakefile.rb
./lib/binman/rakefile.rb:29:in \fB\fCload'
./lib/binman/rakefile.rb:29:in\fRblock in <top (required)>'
Tasks: TOP => build => binman => binman:man
(See full trace by running task with \-\-trace)
exit 1
.IP \(bu 2
Show HTML manual only as fallback to TTY man page.
.PP
This prevents annoying browser launches every time you run \fB\fC\-\-help\fR\&.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\fCBinMan::show()\fR didn't always fallback to plain text header.
.IP \(bu 2
Don't override \fB\fCman \-P\fR pager; set \fB\fC$LESS\fR and \fB\fC$MORE\fR instead.
.PP
Also, shell escaping the pattern prevents you from using regexp syntax.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB\fCman FILE\fR isn't portable; use \fB\fCman \-M ...\fR instead.
.PP
\fB\fCman FILE\fR used to work in Debian, but doesn't work under Void Linux.
.PP
\fB\fCman \-l FILE\fR works in Linux and OpenBSD but not on MacOSX / FreeBSD.
.PP
Therefore, avoid all this portability mess using \fB\fCman \-M ...\fR instead.
.IP \(bu 2
Handle case where roff manual page is missing but HTML version exists.
.RE
.SH Version 4.0.0 (2014\-10\-26)
.SS Major:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.BR binman (1): 
Rename the \fB\fCload\fR command to \fB\fCsnip\fR and remove \fB\fCconv\fR\&.
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
The \fB\fCbinman conv\fR command has been removed; use \fB\fCmd2man\-roff\fR instead.
.IP \(bu 2
We no longer require a specific md2man version at runtime; any will do.
.RE
.IP \(bu 2
Upgrade to md2man 4.0, which no longer expands cross references in code
spans and code blocks.  Your manuals might be rendered differently now.
.RE
.SH Version 3.4.1 (2014\-07\-01)
.PP
This release fixes the help options' REGEXP argument under non\-Debian systems.
.SS Patch:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.BR pager (1) 
isn't a universal command: CentOS uses \fB\fCless \-is\fR instead.
.IP \(bu 2
Silence 
.BR man (1) 
stderr when displaying dynamically extracted manual.
.RE
.SS Other:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
README: add intro hook and source+result examples.
.IP \(bu 2
Document REGEXP argument for help options in \fB\fCbin/*\fR\&.
.IP \(bu 2
Refer to REGEXP argument as PATTERN like less does.
.RE
.SH Version 3.4.0 (2014\-06\-29)
.SS Minor:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
GH\-3: add optional regexp argument to \fB\fC\-h\fR/\fB\fC\-\-help\fR to search in 
.BR man (1).
.PP
The \fB\fC\-h\fR and \fB\fC\-\-help\fR options in \fB\fCBinMan.help()\fR can now be optionally
followed by a regular expression argument that specifies text to search
for and, if found, jump to inside the displayed UNIX man page.  Such a
regular expression argument can now also be passed into \fB\fCBinMan.show()\fR\&.
.RE
.SS Other:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
README: add syntax highlighting to code snippets.
.RE
